The paper discusses the use of DNA cryptography and hash functions for authentication and protection of sensitive information, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of social networks and databases for these purposes also suggests relevance to cybernetics (cs.CY) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the potential use of DNA sequencers in smartphones, which could fall under the categories of databases (cs.DB) and systems and control (cs.SY).
